BIO_HERO_DESC:
Was born in Yerevan, Armenia in 1986. After taking his bachelor's and masters degrees in homeland, he moved to Warsaw  in 2012 and completed a six-month study with the
composer Paweł Mykietyn. From 2012 to 2018 Arsen Babajanyan continued his
master studies at the University of Music and Performing Arts Munich in the composition
class of Prof. Jan Müller-Wieland. Simaltenously he completed  Postgraduation in Conservatory for Music and Theater, Graz  in subject "Composition and Music Theory"
 with  Prof. Beat Furrer.
